The Court ruled today that Alabama likely violated the Voting Rights Act by creating a map that diluted Black votes in the state. This decision affirms the principle that voting practices should not discriminate based on race. However, there is still work to be done. Vice President Harris and the speaker of the article will continue to fight for the passage of the John Lewis Voting Rights Advancement Act and the Freedom to Vote Act. These acts aim to restore and strengthen the Voting Rights Act and ensure fair Congressional maps, respectively.